The government of Lagos State on Wednesday  announced the recovery and discharge of 49 COVID-19 patients, the highest single figure of recovery in the state and Nigeria. The Lagos State Ministry of Health, through its verified Twitter handle on Wednesday, said the patients were 28 females and 21 males including a foreign national – a Greek citizen. It said that they were discharged from the Yaba and Onikan Isolation facilities to reunite with the society. ️”The patients; 18 from IDH, Yaba and 31 from Onikan Isolation Centre have fully recovered and tested negative to #COVID19 in two consecutive readings. *With this, number of patients successfully managed and discharged in Lagos is now 187,” it said.